1
00:01:30,258 --> 00:01:32,260
There was no one like Hal.

2
00:01:32,469 --> 00:01:35,054
He met me at a party
and swept me off my feet.

3
00:01:35,263 --> 00:01:36,765
"Blue Moon" was playing.

4
00:01:36,973 --> 00:01:38,475
- You know "Blue Moon?"
- Sure.

5
00:01:38,683 --> 00:01:40,894
I still remember that.

6
00:01:42,854 --> 00:01:46,149
And one more year
and I would have graduated.

7
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:50,195
But I quit BU to marry him. I mean,
what was I learning at school anyway?

8
00:01:50,403 --> 00:01:53,948
I mean, can you picture me
as an anthropologist?

9
00:01:55,492 --> 00:01:56,993
Is that a joke?

10
00:01:57,202 --> 00:02:00,538
The sex was always great.
Well, he was nine years older than me.

11
00:02:00,747 --> 00:02:02,749
He'd already made and lost a fortune.

12
00:02:02,957 --> 00:02:06,002
But then he made it back, and more.
I mean, much more.

13
00:02:06,211 --> 00:02:07,504
God, he was dynamic.

14
00:02:07,712 --> 00:02:10,423
Taught me everything I know
about real lovemaking...

15
00:02:10,632 --> 00:02:12,842
...not that I care to get too graphic.

16
00:02:13,051 --> 00:02:16,262
Believe me when I tell you.
They tried six medications on me.

17
00:02:16,471 --> 00:02:18,097
Cocktails, they call them.

18
00:02:18,306 --> 00:02:20,892
The only cocktail that helped
was a Stoli martini.

19
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:22,352
I never trusted doctors.

20
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:25,188
Doctors put both my parents
in early graves.

21
00:02:25,396 --> 00:02:27,232
I have never been to San Francisco.

22
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:30,443
And Hal and I traveled everywhere.
I hear it's beautiful.

23
00:02:30,652 --> 00:02:33,488
I'll be staying with my sister, Ginger.
She's divorced.

24
00:02:33,696 --> 00:02:37,909
Biologically, she's not my sister.
She's adopted. We're both adopted.

25
00:02:38,117 --> 00:02:40,870
I couldn't stand her ex-husband.
He used to hit her.

26
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:43,039
That's mine. The Vuitton.

27
00:02:43,248 --> 00:02:46,125
My plan is to start a new life out here.

28
00:02:46,334 --> 00:02:48,962
Put everything behind me
and start fresh.

29
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:53,383
Go West. Was it Horace Greeley
who said that? "Go West."

30
00:02:53,591 --> 00:02:56,886
Oh, there's my family.
It was really nice talking to you.

31
00:02:57,095 --> 00:02:59,681
Oh, I'll call you, maybe for lunch.

32
00:02:59,889 --> 00:03:02,225
I don't have your number.

33
00:03:02,976 --> 00:03:07,272
- Who's that woman you were talking to?
- I was sitting next to her on the plane.

34
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,898
She was talking to herself.

35
00:03:09,107 --> 00:03:11,776
I thought she said something to me.
I said, "What?"

36
00:03:11,985 --> 00:03:14,988
But she couldn't stop babbling
about her life.

37
00:03:32,171 --> 00:03:34,674
Where--? Where am I exactly?

38
00:03:34,883 --> 00:03:38,094
You said 305 South Van Ness.

39
00:03:44,058 --> 00:03:47,312
- Can you wait, help me with my bags?
- Sure.

40
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:55,069
I don't know where she is.

41
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,488
She expected me.

42
00:03:58,031 --> 00:04:00,658
The plane was on time.

43
00:04:07,248 --> 00:04:08,625
- Yes, I'm--
- You all right?

44
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:12,795
I'm fine. I just sometimes get
where I can't take a deep breath...

45
00:04:13,004 --> 00:04:17,884
...and when I can, it makes me panic
and it makes it even worse.

46
00:04:18,092 --> 00:04:19,761
Okay.

47
00:04:21,512 --> 00:04:24,015
- Could I have some privacy?
- Sure, sure.

48
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:25,975
Hello, Ginger?

49
00:04:26,184 --> 00:04:28,645
Yes, I'm here.
I'm right in front of the place.

50
00:04:28,853 --> 00:04:30,980
It is 305?

51
00:04:33,691 --> 00:04:35,860
Well, how long?

52
00:04:36,152 --> 00:04:39,155
What? Where is it?

53
00:04:39,364 --> 00:04:42,867
No, no, I see it. Okay. Oh, okay.

54
00:04:43,076 --> 00:04:46,537
Just-- Would you please hurry?
My sister left the keys in the bar.

55
00:04:46,746 --> 00:04:48,706
- Can you wait?
- Sure!

56
00:05:11,354 --> 00:05:12,981
Is that it?

57
00:05:16,526 --> 00:05:18,277
Thank you.

58
00:05:19,362 --> 00:05:21,197
Oh, thank you.

59
00:05:21,406 --> 00:05:24,409
Have a great day, all right? Bye-bye.

60
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,416
- So, what do you think?
- I love it.

61
00:05:31,624 --> 00:05:34,544
The fireplaces work.
I don't like when they're for show.

62
00:05:34,752 --> 00:05:37,547
It's so light and airy
and the ceilings are so high.

63
00:05:37,755 --> 00:05:40,591
How can anyone breathe
with a low ceiling? The view...

64
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,386
- You wanted Fifth Avenue.
- Central Park. Superb.

65
00:05:43,594 --> 00:05:45,304
Oh, this space is perfect.

66
00:05:45,513 --> 00:05:47,223
We hardly have to do a thing.

67
00:05:47,432 --> 00:05:49,767
- You shouldn't spoil me so.
- Well, why not?

68
00:05:49,976 --> 00:05:52,562
Who else am I gonna spoil?
Did I tell you my news?

69
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:54,897
- What?
- Danny is gonna be living with us.

70
00:05:55,106 --> 00:05:57,150
Oh, honey. Oh, that's great news.

71
00:05:57,358 --> 00:05:59,527
I worked it outwith his mom,
her lawyers.

72
00:05:59,736 --> 00:06:03,948
Oh, he'll be so much happier
when he's with us full-time.

73
00:06:05,950 --> 00:06:08,119
Happy birthday, Danny.

74
00:06:08,745 --> 00:06:12,540
Kids at school say we're really rich
and that you give money to charity.

75
00:06:12,749 --> 00:06:15,585
Sure I do. You gotta remember
as you go through life...

76
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:18,504
...to share what you earn
with the less fortunate.

77
00:06:18,713 --> 00:06:21,424
Not everyone is as lucky as we are.

78
00:06:21,632 --> 00:06:22,759
- Domingo?
- Yes, ma'am.

79
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:25,720
- Another bottle of the Margaux.
- Sure.

80
00:06:26,137 --> 00:06:27,180
Excuse me.

81
00:06:27,388 --> 00:06:29,766
- It would look perfect.
- Wouldn't wash me out?

82
00:06:29,974 --> 00:06:31,684
No, not at all. Not the way he--

83
00:06:31,893 --> 00:06:34,562
Oh, isn't he sweet?

84
00:06:34,771 --> 00:06:38,149
This song was playing
when Hal and I first met.

85
00:06:38,858 --> 00:06:42,445
- I fell in love with the name Jasmine.
- Oh, so romantic.

86
00:06:43,112 --> 00:06:45,281
Ichangedit

87
00:06:45,490 --> 00:06:48,826
Yeah, Jeanette had no panache.

88
00:06:51,829 --> 00:06:54,165
This song was playing
when we first met.

89
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:58,419
You know it? Yeah, we met
at a party at Martha's Vineyard.

90
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,838
"Blue Moon."

91
00:07:01,798 --> 00:07:03,800
Come on, boys.

92
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:08,096
Okay, let's go, Augie.
I gotta get home. Someone's waiting.

93
00:07:08,304 --> 00:07:10,306
We helped Dad
move the furniture today.

94
00:07:10,515 --> 00:07:13,184
Oh, really? That's your idea
of taking the boys?

95
00:07:13,392 --> 00:07:16,312
Letting them help you
lug somebody's furniture upstairs?

96
00:07:16,521 --> 00:07:18,481
- They loved it. Great exercise.
- Yeah?

97
00:07:18,689 --> 00:07:21,442
- They-- We ate franks and beans.
- Yeah.

98
00:07:21,651 --> 00:07:24,487
- Relax.
- Okay. Let's go, Johnny, come on.

99
00:07:24,695 --> 00:07:27,490
- Come on. Let's go. Come on.
- What's the rush?

100
00:07:27,698 --> 00:07:29,909
What's the rush, Ginger?
You got a date?

101
00:07:30,118 --> 00:07:31,577
It's none of your business.

102
00:07:31,786 --> 00:07:35,081
- It happens to be Jeanette, so...
- Jeanefie?

103
00:07:35,289 --> 00:07:37,166
Jasmine? What is she doing in town?

104
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:40,086
She's living with me
till she gets back on her feet.

105
00:07:40,294 --> 00:07:42,004
She's had a bad time. Yeah.

106
00:07:42,213 --> 00:07:44,966
When she had money,
she wanted nothing to do with you.

107
00:07:45,174 --> 00:07:47,176
Now that she's broke, she's moving in.

108
00:07:47,385 --> 00:07:49,387
She's not just broke.
She's screwed up.

109
00:07:49,595 --> 00:07:52,140
And it's none of your damn business.
She's family.

110
00:07:52,348 --> 00:07:53,850
- She stole our money.
- Okay.

111
00:07:54,058 --> 00:07:58,187
Understand? We could have been set.
That was our whole chance in life.

112
00:07:58,396 --> 00:08:02,483
For the last time, Augie,
he was the crook, not her, okay?

113
00:08:02,692 --> 00:08:04,819
What the hell did she know
aboutfinance?

114
00:08:05,027 --> 00:08:08,823
Don't stand there and tell me that.
She's married to a guy for years...

115
00:08:09,031 --> 00:08:11,868
...up to his ass in phony real estate
and bank fraud.

116
00:08:12,076 --> 00:08:13,703
She knew nothing about it?

117
00:08:13,911 --> 00:08:17,498
Believe me, she knew, Ginger.
Okay? She knew.

118
00:08:17,707 --> 00:08:20,710
But when all those diamonds
and minks were flying in...

119
00:08:20,918 --> 00:08:24,046
...she just looked the other way.
- I don't think so, Augie.

120
00:08:24,255 --> 00:08:29,552
You said it. You said to me,
"She's a phony and had to know."

121
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,972
Jasmine, your country house
is so beautiful.

122
00:08:33,181 --> 00:08:35,808
- See?
- I'm sorry, but we need an answer on this.

123
00:08:36,017 --> 00:08:38,686
I told you, you change the name
of the corporation.

124
00:08:38,895 --> 00:08:41,981
- Operate under Global Innovations.
- I don't know if we can.

125
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,524
I think we can, actually.

126
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:46,360
- Pay out of the accounts in Amsterdam.
- Amsterdam.

127
00:08:46,569 --> 00:08:50,364
Whenever I hear them, they're one step
ahead of the Justice Department.

128
00:08:50,573 --> 00:08:52,408
Just hope your house is not bugged.

129
00:08:52,617 --> 00:08:55,453
Oh, I never pay attention
to Hal's business affairs.

130
00:08:55,661 --> 00:08:57,663
I have no head for that sort of thing.

131
00:08:57,872 --> 00:09:01,250
- We transfer to the old corporation?
- We could. Perfectly legal.

132
00:09:01,459 --> 00:09:05,713
- It would be a mistake under that name.
- Definitely get in trouble for that.

133
00:09:05,922 --> 00:09:08,132
Just don't file a joint tax return.

134
00:09:08,341 --> 00:09:12,011
Don't say that. I sign anything.
I'm very trusting.

135
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:13,554
Famous last words.

136
00:09:13,763 --> 00:09:16,140
It's called looking the other way.

137
00:09:18,476 --> 00:09:21,229
Jasmine. Oh, my God.

138
00:09:21,437 --> 00:09:23,397
- Look at you.
- Look at you.

139
00:09:23,606 --> 00:09:26,025
Oh, I am so sorry for the wait.

140
00:09:26,234 --> 00:09:28,444
- Sorry, I think I'm in Paris.
- It's okay.

141
00:09:28,653 --> 00:09:30,947
- No, it's fine.
- Augie's day with the boys.

142
00:09:31,155 --> 00:09:32,907
Well, no wonder you're late.

143
00:09:33,115 --> 00:09:34,825
- Hello. Matthew, is it?
- Yeah.

144
00:09:35,034 --> 00:09:37,620
Boys, say hello.
I told you about her, remember?

145
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:40,289
- Hi, I'm Jasmine.
- Shake hands. Okay, go play.

146
00:09:40,498 --> 00:09:41,916
- They're big.
- I know.

147
00:09:42,124 --> 00:09:44,252
- I'm getting it first.
- Quiet, you two.

148
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:47,088
- Well, they're loud.
- Stop running around.

149
00:09:47,296 --> 00:09:50,049
Christ, this kid's got--
What the hell is it? ADD?

150
00:09:50,258 --> 00:09:54,720
- Yeah. Your place is homey.
- Are you kidding me?

151
00:09:54,929 --> 00:09:58,474
No, I mean, it's got a very--
Well, it's casual charm.

152
00:09:58,683 --> 00:10:01,352
God, knock it oh', Jasmine.

153
00:10:02,311 --> 00:10:06,065
I need to stay here for a while. No, I do.

154
00:10:06,649 --> 00:10:08,693
- I'm out of cash.
- Okay.

155
00:10:08,901 --> 00:10:11,612
Couldn't pay my rent in Brooklyn.
Can you believe...

156
00:10:11,821 --> 00:10:14,824
...I had to move out of my home,
take a place in Brooklyn?

157
00:10:15,032 --> 00:10:18,119
But I'm dead broke. Really,
the government took everything.

158
00:10:18,327 --> 00:10:19,996
And the lawyers.

159
00:10:20,204 --> 00:10:21,831
And I can't be alone, Ginger.

160
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:24,625
I really get some bad thoughts
when I'm alone.

161
00:10:24,834 --> 00:10:28,337
Well, you know, all I can say is,
you look great.

162
00:10:29,422 --> 00:10:31,799
- Now who's lying?
- You do.

163
00:10:32,008 --> 00:10:34,844
You know, I was up all last night.
I was so anxious...

164
00:10:35,052 --> 00:10:36,554
...about moving here.
- Yeah?

165
00:10:36,762 --> 00:10:40,474
- I wasn't sure how angry you still were.
- Oh, well...

166
00:10:41,726 --> 00:10:44,562
- Another drink? We're celebrating.
- Of course, yeah.

167
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:47,023
Oh, the flight was bumpy.

168
00:10:47,231 --> 00:10:51,360
I didn't eat anything on the plane.
Oh, the food was awful. Here it is.

169
00:10:51,569 --> 00:10:54,405
I mean, you'd think first class, right?

170
00:10:54,947 --> 00:10:56,490
You flew first class?

171
00:10:56,699 --> 00:10:59,410
I don't know how anyone puts up
with those airlines.

172
00:10:59,618 --> 00:11:03,331
- Isn't first class a fortune?
- Yes, I was quite shocked.

173
00:11:03,539 --> 00:11:07,460
- I thought you were tapped out.
- I'm worse than tapped out, baby.

174
00:11:07,668 --> 00:11:09,879
I've run up some serious debts.

175
00:11:10,087 --> 00:11:11,881
So how did you fly first class?

176
00:11:12,089 --> 00:11:15,926
I don't know, Ginger. I just did.

177
00:11:16,635 --> 00:11:19,889
All I meant was, if you've got no money,
to go first class...

178
00:11:20,097 --> 00:11:22,892
You know me. I splurge from habit.

179
00:11:24,101 --> 00:11:27,146
Would you stop staring
at my luggage?

180
00:11:27,355 --> 00:11:29,523
Yes, it's Louis Vuitton.

181
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:33,402
- You told me you had to sell everything.
- Look, look, look.

182
00:11:33,611 --> 00:11:37,406
These are used, old suitcases.
See, with my initials. Who'd want them?

183
00:11:37,615 --> 00:11:40,951
I sold what jewels and furs
I could hide from Uncle Sam.

184
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,995
God, I hate to tell you about that.

185
00:11:43,204 --> 00:11:47,458
Jewelry is priceless, a great investment
when you buy it at Graff or Van Cleef...

186
00:11:47,666 --> 00:11:50,669
...until you're desperate for money
and forced to sell...

187
00:11:50,878 --> 00:11:53,464
...and then it seems
you can't give it away.

188
00:11:54,965 --> 00:11:57,885
Kids, stop it, come on!

189
00:11:58,427 --> 00:12:00,846
- Were you adopted?
- Yes.

190
00:12:01,055 --> 00:12:02,890
We were both adopted.

191
00:12:03,099 --> 00:12:06,769
Born to different moms and dads,
but raised by the same mom and dad.

192
00:12:06,977 --> 00:12:09,605
Could you stop doing that gun thing?
Sorry.

193
00:12:09,814 --> 00:12:12,858
- Got migraine from the pressurized cabin.
- Matthew.

194
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:15,194
Did you like the new mom and dad?

195
00:12:15,403 --> 00:12:17,363
- Yes, of course--
- Aunt Jasmine did.

196
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:20,741
I ran away from home
as fast as my feet could carry me.

197
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:22,952
- How come?
- Well--

198
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,621
Our mother liked Aunt Jasmine
and not me.

199
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:27,915
- Oh, stop.
- How come?

200
00:12:28,124 --> 00:12:30,459
- She had better genes.
- Don't tell them that.

201
00:12:30,668 --> 00:12:34,130
- Well, am I lying?
- Dad said you're glad we lived far away.

202
00:12:34,338 --> 00:12:35,965
What?

203
00:12:36,173 --> 00:12:39,718
They're perfect for the dress
that I'm wearing to the Met Gala.

204
00:12:41,679 --> 00:12:44,473
What's the matter?
Your mind is a million miles away.

205
00:12:44,682 --> 00:12:49,645
Oh, I'm sorry. No, I--
I just got a call from my sister, Ginger.

206
00:12:49,854 --> 00:12:54,150
Oh, God, she's coming to New York
for a week with her husband, Augie.

207
00:12:54,358 --> 00:12:55,818
He is a piece of work.

208
00:12:56,026 --> 00:12:58,612
I just-- I don't know,
I guess I have to see them.

209
00:12:58,821 --> 00:13:01,198
- The one in San Francisco, the builder?
- Yeah.

210
00:13:01,407 --> 00:13:05,077
Oh, no, he's a contractor.
I mean, he's-- No, he's a handyman.

211
00:13:05,286 --> 00:13:08,414
No, don't get me wrong.
I love Ginger, I do. She's a dear.

212
00:13:08,622 --> 00:13:11,542
But our paths just went
in totally different directions.

213
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:12,835
Okay, that happens.

214
00:13:13,043 --> 00:13:16,046
It's terrible of me to say,
but she was never too bright.

215
00:13:16,255 --> 00:13:19,717
You know? And she was so wild
and I, of course, was Miss Perfect.

216
00:13:21,719 --> 00:13:23,596
- Hi.
- Oh, you made it.

217
00:13:23,804 --> 00:13:25,848
- How lovely to see you.
- Hi. Oh, my God.

218
00:13:26,056 --> 00:13:27,641
- Welcome.
- Hi. Thank you.

219
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:30,019
- Oh, this is my husband, Augie.
- Augie.

220
00:13:30,227 --> 00:13:32,396
- This is Jeanette.
- Jasmine. I changed it.

221
00:13:32,605 --> 00:13:35,191
- Jasmine.
- I'm finally getting to meet the sister.

222
00:13:35,399 --> 00:13:39,278
I know. Hello. I'm so sorry
we couldn't make it to the wedding.

223
00:13:39,487 --> 00:13:41,989
Just that Hal had some business
in Saint-Tropez.

224
00:13:42,198 --> 00:13:44,200
- Couldn't get back in time.
- Know what?

225
00:13:44,408 --> 00:13:47,828
You missed a nice little party.
My friend Dennis sang.

226
00:13:48,037 --> 00:13:50,539
- He's great. Dennis Rackabuto.
- I know. Hey--

227
00:13:50,748 --> 00:13:53,417
Hal! You remember Ginger.

228
00:13:53,626 --> 00:13:55,002
- Oh, my gosh.
- How are you?

229
00:13:55,211 --> 00:13:56,712
- How are you?
- This is Augie.

230
00:13:56,921 --> 00:13:58,589
- Augie. How you doing?
- Awesome.

231
00:13:58,797 --> 00:14:00,716
- Hell of a place you got.
- Thank you.

232
00:14:00,925 --> 00:14:02,801
- Why don't you come through?
- Told you.

233
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,887
- Yvette, coffee?
- This is really...

234
00:14:05,095 --> 00:14:06,263
Yeah, she's got taste.

235
00:14:06,472 --> 00:14:08,432
It's like what you see in the movies.

236
00:14:08,641 --> 00:14:12,394
We have so much to catch up on.
Can't wait for you to show us New York.

237
00:14:12,603 --> 00:14:14,605
Why don't you take our car and driver?

238
00:14:14,813 --> 00:14:18,067
Well, I hope you're gonna come.
I mean, how often am I here?

239
00:14:18,275 --> 00:14:21,946
- No, no, I will definitely make some time.
- Oh, good.

240
00:14:24,073 --> 00:14:25,241
Where are you staying?

241
00:14:25,449 --> 00:14:28,953
Oh, well, we-- We thought about asking
if we could stay with you...

242
00:14:29,161 --> 00:14:32,581
...but we don't wanna impose,
so we got a room at the Marriott.

243
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,625
- Oh, the Marriott's perfect.
- Yeah.

244
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:37,836
I'll have my office contact them
and forward us the bill.

245
00:14:38,045 --> 00:14:40,256
- Oh, no.
- No, no, no, it's not necessary.

246
00:14:40,464 --> 00:14:42,591
Please, you're our guests. I insist.

247
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:46,220
Oh, well, then we insist
on taking you two to dinner tonight.

248
00:14:46,804 --> 00:14:49,765
- What? Tonight?
- Yeah.

249
00:14:50,015 --> 00:14:52,560
We have dinner plans.

250
00:14:52,768 --> 00:14:55,688
I don't think we can--
Something we can't get out of.

251
00:14:55,896 --> 00:14:57,398
- I'm sorry.
- There'll be time.

252
00:14:57,606 --> 00:15:00,901
We stashed the kids with Augie's sister,
we're here for a week.

253
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:02,945
- It's gonna be great.
- It is. Okay.

254
00:15:03,153 --> 00:15:05,698
Well, we don't have a lot of free time...

255
00:15:05,906 --> 00:15:08,826
...but we'll definitely take you
to Le Cirque, won't we?

256
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:10,452
I mean, or Daniel. I mean--

257
00:15:10,661 --> 00:15:13,455
- They'd get a kick out of that.
- Yeah, absolutely.

258
00:15:13,664 --> 00:15:17,918
I know your birthday is this week.
Let us at least take you out for that.

259
00:15:19,712 --> 00:15:23,465
- I love how you're doing your hair.
- Oh, thanks.

260
00:15:23,674 --> 00:15:27,928
You'll have to take me shopping.
You always could pick clothes.

261
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:32,308
And Augie's got
some exciting business news...

262
00:15:32,516 --> 00:15:34,643
...he wants to talk to Hal about.

263
00:15:34,852 --> 00:15:37,688
Don't worry, I don't need
to borrow money. We're flush.

264
00:15:37,896 --> 00:15:40,107
- Yeah,
- What kind of work do you do, Augie?

265
00:15:40,316 --> 00:15:43,652
Well, you know,
I do, like, repairs, furniture moving...

266
00:15:43,861 --> 00:15:45,863
...but I got plans to be my own boss.

267
00:15:46,071 --> 00:15:48,741
We'll talk about it over dinner.
They're going out.

268
00:15:48,949 --> 00:15:50,367
Hey, could we have a tour?

269
00:15:50,576 --> 00:15:54,830
Oh, yeah, of course.
Why don't you start in the kitchen?

270
00:15:55,039 --> 00:15:58,125
- Is there a little girls' room?
- Just down the hall.

271
00:15:59,543 --> 00:16:01,086
Five days.

272
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:04,006
I'll have to invite them
to my birthday party now.

273
00:16:04,214 --> 00:16:08,010
- Where did she come up with him?
- I always feel so guilty around Ginger.

274
00:16:08,218 --> 00:16:11,013
We've got to make sure
we make their stay extra nice.

275
00:16:11,221 --> 00:16:14,224
My God, five days.

276
00:16:16,477 --> 00:16:18,437
Look.

277
00:16:19,396 --> 00:16:22,149
It's so beautiful.

278
00:16:22,358 --> 00:16:24,360
Oh, but where would I wear
a Fendi bag?

279
00:16:24,568 --> 00:16:26,737
Oh, go ahead. It's my treat.

280
00:16:26,945 --> 00:16:29,073
- No.
- Yeah.

281
00:16:29,281 --> 00:16:30,991
Really?

282
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,286
Oh, my God. I love it. Look.

283
00:16:34,495 --> 00:16:35,704
Look.

284
00:16:35,913 --> 00:16:38,707
- Take the other one off.
- No, I like this.

285
00:16:40,876 --> 00:16:44,797
Boy, this is some place you got here.

286
00:16:45,005 --> 00:16:47,299
- I mean, this is unreal.
- It is.

287
00:16:47,508 --> 00:16:49,259
Reminds me of when I was a kid.

288
00:16:49,468 --> 00:16:50,886
I used to be a lifeguard.

289
00:16:51,095 --> 00:16:53,722
Start your own construction company?
Great idea.

290
00:16:53,931 --> 00:16:56,392
- We came into some money.
- Tell him how, Augie.

291
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,894
- We've been saving this story.
- What?

292
00:16:59,103 --> 00:17:02,648
Well, the first 10-, 12,000,
I really worked for.

293
00:17:02,856 --> 00:17:04,483
Put away a little each week.

294
00:17:04,692 --> 00:17:06,694
But he's not telling you the big news.

295
00:17:06,902 --> 00:17:08,987
- Why we're in New York.
- You tell them.

296
00:17:09,196 --> 00:17:11,240
Okay, I will.

297
00:17:11,448 --> 00:17:12,950
We always play the lottery...

298
00:17:13,158 --> 00:17:16,370
...and we never even get two numbers.
Am I right?

299
00:17:16,578 --> 00:17:18,080
But last week, we hit it.

300
00:17:18,288 --> 00:17:20,165
We got 200,000 bucks.

301
00:17:20,374 --> 00:17:22,751
Oh, that's fantastic.

302
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,003
- I thought I'd drop dead.
- That's great.

303
00:17:25,212 --> 00:17:28,257
I never held that kind of money
in my hands. I mean, ever.

304
00:17:28,465 --> 00:17:30,050
He was shaking when we won.

305
00:17:30,259 --> 00:17:34,263
Me? You had to see her. I had to tell her,
this is a once-in-a-lifetime.

306
00:17:34,471 --> 00:17:36,098
- Congratulations.
- Yeah.

307
00:17:36,306 --> 00:17:39,435
He wants to begin a business.
What do you think?

308
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:44,189
Well, if you like, I think Hal
could probably help you do better.

309
00:17:44,398 --> 00:17:45,441
Yeah?

310
00:17:45,649 --> 00:17:50,279
You know-- You know, I'm no gambler.
I mean, not with my one chance to--

311
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:54,575
Hey, come on. We don't know
the first thing about money, but he does.

312
00:17:54,783 --> 00:17:58,162
First thing is how not to give half
your money to the government.

313
00:17:58,370 --> 00:18:01,248
Look, I know there's taxes,
but, I mean, what can I do?

314
00:18:01,457 --> 00:18:03,625
- There are ways.
- You see, Augie? You see?

315
00:18:03,834 --> 00:18:07,504
Suppose I put you in a venture
that was low-risk, but very high-yield.

316
00:18:07,713 --> 00:18:11,258
I'm not talking about 6 or 7 percent.
I'm talking about 20 percent.

317
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:13,135
- Profitable enough?
-20 percent?

318
00:18:13,343 --> 00:18:16,138
He's developing a group of hotels
in the Caribbean.

319
00:18:16,346 --> 00:18:19,475
You mean,
not starting my own business.

320
00:18:19,683 --> 00:18:21,977
No, we mean investing with Hal.

321
00:18:22,186 --> 00:18:25,314
Jeez, investing what?
You mean the whole thing?

322
00:18:25,522 --> 00:18:27,941
You need money to make money.
Am I right?

323
00:18:28,192 --> 00:18:29,234
Ginger.

324
00:18:29,443 --> 00:18:32,321
Let them in on one of your--
The hotel deal or something.

325
00:18:32,529 --> 00:18:34,740
It'd be great for them. Make a killing.

326
00:18:34,948 --> 00:18:37,868
- Pay attention, Augie.
- I'm paying attention.

327
00:18:39,036 --> 00:18:41,079
You will make money for them,
won't you?

328
00:18:41,288 --> 00:18:43,081
I make money, they make money.

329
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:45,083
God, they're hard work.

330
00:18:45,292 --> 00:18:47,336
Tomorrow I'm taking the day off.

331
00:18:47,544 --> 00:18:50,547
I've neglected everything,
my yoga, my Pilates.

332
00:18:50,756 --> 00:18:52,508
I've got that luncheon to plan...

333
00:18:52,716 --> 00:18:55,427
...the fundraiser
for the Central Park Conservancy.

334
00:18:55,636 --> 00:18:57,805
I've rented them a limo and a driver...

335
00:18:58,013 --> 00:19:01,558
...and I've suggested they go
to the South Street Seaport.

336
00:19:01,975 --> 00:19:04,645
Can you imagine if they lived here?

337
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:09,024
Here, for doing your duty.

338
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:11,151
Happy birthday.

339
00:19:11,985 --> 00:19:16,031
I'm giving it to you now so you can wear it
to your party tomorrow night.

340
00:19:16,490 --> 00:19:20,035
Oh, sweetheart, it's beautiful.

341
00:19:20,244 --> 00:19:23,705
Not bad taste
for a philistine businessman, huh?

342
00:20:55,881 --> 00:20:59,051
- I know, it's so extravagant.
- Oh, look at that.

343
00:20:59,259 --> 00:21:01,803
He surprised me in the tub,
so to speak.

344
00:21:02,012 --> 00:21:05,807
Corsica's a bore. The weather's nice,
but it's nothing like Sardinia.

345
00:21:06,016 --> 00:21:09,353
This year you are coming
to Palm Beach, no excuses.

346
00:21:10,479 --> 00:21:13,148
- Hey, Jasmine.
- What?

347
00:21:13,357 --> 00:21:15,776
- Who's that woman?
- Which?

348
00:21:15,984 --> 00:21:17,486
- That one.
- Oh, Raylene.

349
00:21:17,694 --> 00:21:19,780
She's a friend. I love Raylene.

350
00:21:19,988 --> 00:21:21,657
We met in a yoga class.

351
00:21:21,865 --> 00:21:23,617
- Isn't she pretty?
- Yeah.

352
00:21:23,825 --> 00:21:25,577
She runs a modeling agency.

353
00:21:25,786 --> 00:21:28,205
- How long have you known her?
- Few years. Why?

354
00:21:28,747 --> 00:21:31,708
- And you trust her?
- Trust her?

355
00:21:31,917 --> 00:21:35,379
Of course I trust her.
What kind of question is that?

356
00:21:35,587 --> 00:21:38,256
She just seems so cozy all night
with your husband.

357
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:41,885
I wouldn't worry. Hal's not
the roving type, nor is Raylene.

358
00:21:42,094 --> 00:21:44,596
- She's a very close friend.
- I don't know.

359
00:21:44,805 --> 00:21:47,140
If it was my husband,
I'd keep an eye on him.

360
00:21:47,349 --> 00:21:51,269
Goodness, you are a suspicious one.

361
00:21:51,478 --> 00:21:53,188
- I'm just saying.
- Just relax.

362
00:21:53,397 --> 00:21:55,399
I am relaxed.

363
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:58,694
You shouldn't drink so much, Augie.

364
00:21:58,902 --> 00:22:02,322
Nobody wants to hear
those stupid Polish jokes, you know?

365
00:22:02,531 --> 00:22:04,533
Oh, I had a drink?

366
00:22:04,741 --> 00:22:05,784
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

367
00:22:05,993 --> 00:22:10,914
Let me tell you, you were half in the bag
the entire night, okay?

368
00:22:11,123 --> 00:22:13,250
Tell me about my drinking.

369
00:22:13,458 --> 00:22:16,878
- Give me that.
- What's eating you?

370
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:21,633
If you saw your friend's wife kissing
another guy, would you tell your friend?

371
00:22:21,842 --> 00:22:23,635
- What?
- Would you tell your friend?

372
00:22:23,844 --> 00:22:26,096
- I'm talking.
- Tell him what?

373
00:22:27,764 --> 00:22:29,433
Are you listening to me?

374
00:22:29,641 --> 00:22:34,104
If you saw your friend's wife kissing
another guy, would you tell your friend?

375
00:22:34,312 --> 00:22:35,689
- Would you tell him?
- Yeah.

376
00:22:35,897 --> 00:22:38,984
- Bet your ass I'd tell him.
- But what if it causes trouble?

377
00:22:39,192 --> 00:22:40,610
Or maybe a divorce?

378
00:22:40,819 --> 00:22:43,947
If you don't say anything,
it could've been a passing thing.

379
00:22:44,156 --> 00:22:46,825
He never knows and he lives on
happy with his wife.

380
00:22:47,034 --> 00:22:50,746
You know, I would tell him,
because that's what a friend's for.

381
00:22:50,954 --> 00:22:53,915
You gotta have his back.
That's why I'd tell him.

382
00:22:54,124 --> 00:22:56,918
It's a tough call, Augie. I don't know.

383
00:22:58,420 --> 00:22:59,921
- Ginger?
- What?

384
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:02,591
What are we doing?
Are we playing charades?

385
00:23:02,799 --> 00:23:04,259
I mean, come on.

386
00:23:04,468 --> 00:23:06,928
- Did you see something?
- Yeah.

387
00:23:07,137 --> 00:23:09,639
On the street, by accident.

388
00:23:09,848 --> 00:23:13,852
I saw Hal kissing that brunette
who was at the party.

389
00:23:14,478 --> 00:23:18,940
You saw Hal kiss Raylene? Raylene?

390
00:23:19,149 --> 00:23:21,193
You know her name too?

391
00:23:21,526 --> 00:23:23,236
My God, she gets around.

392
00:23:23,445 --> 00:23:26,782
Oh, we were introduced.
Come on, you got nothing to worry about.

393
00:23:26,990 --> 00:23:29,159
- Yeah.
- Nobody could ever take your place.

394
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:33,205
Yeah, believe me,
I wasn't thinking she'd look at you.

395
00:23:33,497 --> 00:23:35,916
- Nobody would ever look at me, right?
- Right.

396
00:23:36,124 --> 00:23:40,003
- You looked at me.
- Yeah, once. It was a mistake.

397
00:23:40,504 --> 00:23:43,799
- All right, listen.
- What?

398
00:23:44,007 --> 00:23:46,343
You think Hal's banging her?

399
00:23:46,927 --> 00:23:49,096
When Jasmine don't wanna
know something...

400
00:23:49,304 --> 00:23:52,265
...she's got a habit
of looking the other way.

401
00:23:52,474 --> 00:23:55,685
Thank you for my present.
I got so many comments.

402
00:23:55,894 --> 00:23:59,189
I think everyone enjoyed themselves
and that piano player was--

403
00:23:59,397 --> 00:24:01,900
He was fantastic. I got his card.

404
00:24:02,109 --> 00:24:06,154
What were you talking to Raylene
so intensely about?

405
00:24:06,363 --> 00:24:10,242
Oh, her husband is thinking about
getting his own plane.

406
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:15,247
I was just weighing the pros and cons
for her of a Challenger versus a--

407
00:24:15,455 --> 00:24:18,083
- Gulf stream?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

408
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:20,877
- She's so pretty.
- Yeah.

409
00:24:21,086 --> 00:24:24,339
Bill's out of town for a couple weeks
and she'll be all alone.

410
00:24:24,548 --> 00:24:28,718
I thought maybe we could take her out
to dinner or have her over here.

411
00:24:29,177 --> 00:24:30,720
- Yeah.
- Great.

412
00:24:30,929 --> 00:24:32,556
Sure.

413
00:24:37,853 --> 00:24:39,688
- This is silly, Ginger.
- Why?

414
00:24:39,896 --> 00:24:41,022
- It's Sunday.
- So?

415
00:24:41,231 --> 00:24:44,401
It's his day off.
He wants to spend it alone with you.

416
00:24:44,609 --> 00:24:46,403
He's alone with me plenty.

417
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:50,073
If I'm gonna marry Chili,
you're gonna meet him sooner than later.

418
00:24:50,282 --> 00:24:52,117
I told him we'd show you the town.

419
00:24:52,325 --> 00:24:56,413
- Well, he won't want your sister around.
- Will you stop it?

420
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:00,292
This city is so beautifully European.

421
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:02,419
Have you ever been abroad?

422
00:25:02,627 --> 00:25:04,129
- At all?
- No.

423
00:25:04,337 --> 00:25:07,465
We used to sail
from Saint-Tropez to Cannes...

424
00:25:07,674 --> 00:25:09,926
...and up the coast to Monaco.

425
00:25:10,427 --> 00:25:13,555
- It reminds me of the Mediterranean.
- There's Chili.

426
00:25:13,763 --> 00:25:15,599
- Which one?
- There.

427
00:25:15,807 --> 00:25:17,684
- Who's that with him?
- I don't know.

428
00:25:18,226 --> 00:25:19,853
- Chili.
- Hi.

429
00:25:20,061 --> 00:25:21,897
- Hi, hey.
- You look beautiful.

430
00:25:22,105 --> 00:25:24,024
- Oh, thanks.
- Yeah.

431
00:25:24,274 --> 00:25:26,067
- You smell good too.
- You're late.

432
00:25:26,276 --> 00:25:29,279
- Eddie. Nice to meet you.
- Hi. Ginger. Hi.

433
00:25:29,487 --> 00:25:30,572
This is Jasmine.

434
00:25:30,780 --> 00:25:32,866
- Jasmine, hi. I'm Eddie.
- This is Eddie.

435
00:25:33,074 --> 00:25:35,243
- Nice to meet you. Eddie.
- I'm Jasmine.

436
00:25:35,452 --> 00:25:37,120
- Hi.
- Ginger told me about you.

437
00:25:37,329 --> 00:25:39,581
Oh, all good, I hope.

438
00:25:39,789 --> 00:25:43,043
I gotta tell you, I was all set
to move in with your sister.

439
00:25:43,251 --> 00:25:46,922
Then she tells me that we gotta postpone
because her sister's in town.

440
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:50,008
- He's joking.
- Well, I hope I didn't inconvenience you.

441
00:25:50,217 --> 00:25:51,426
It was an emergency.

442
00:25:51,885 --> 00:25:53,678
- No.
- Things happen. Right, Eddie?

443
00:25:53,887 --> 00:25:55,680
Could've happened to anybody.

444
00:25:55,889 --> 00:25:58,475
Told me you never been here,
don't know anybody...

445
00:25:58,683 --> 00:26:01,603
...so I brought along this sad excuse
for a blind date.

446
00:26:01,811 --> 00:26:04,606
- Best he could do on short notice.
- He works with me.

447
00:26:04,814 --> 00:26:06,107
I gotta get a beer.

448
00:26:06,316 --> 00:26:08,610
- You want a beer?
- Can I buy you a drink?

449
00:26:08,818 --> 00:26:11,988
- I have a drink, but thank you.
- I'm dropping dead of hunger.

450
00:26:12,197 --> 00:26:14,282
This place has the best clams.

451
00:26:14,491 --> 00:26:15,992
You like clams, Jasmine?

452
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:18,119
No, no, no. I'm not hungry.

453
00:26:18,620 --> 00:26:21,623
What the hell are you drinking?
Let me see. What is this?

454
00:26:21,831 --> 00:26:22,999
- Is it vodka?
- Martini.

455
00:26:23,208 --> 00:26:26,878
- This place has the best clams in the city.
- The best are at Manero's.

456
00:26:27,087 --> 00:26:29,965
- You're nuts. They don't even compare.
- Who cares?

457
00:26:30,173 --> 00:26:33,718
This place is good too. They're fresh.
That's the thing with clams.

458
00:26:33,927 --> 00:26:36,930
You get a bad clam,
you'll wish you were never born.

459
00:26:37,138 --> 00:26:40,475
- So, what do you do, Jasmine?
- I told you, she just got here.

460
00:26:40,684 --> 00:26:42,519
- She's looking for a job.
- Yeah?

461
00:26:42,852 --> 00:26:45,313
I know a dentist who's looking for help.

462
00:26:45,522 --> 00:26:47,565
- Oh, yeah?
- No, I'm actually thinking...

463
00:26:47,774 --> 00:26:50,193
...of going back to school.
- School?

464
00:26:51,194 --> 00:26:53,113
To study what?

465
00:26:54,656 --> 00:26:57,575
I don't know. I mean,
the biggest mistake I made...

466
00:26:57,784 --> 00:27:01,997
...was leaving college in my last year
and not completing my education.

467
00:27:02,205 --> 00:27:03,498
What would you be?

468
00:27:03,707 --> 00:27:05,292
An anthropologist.

469
00:27:06,001 --> 00:27:08,503
Really? Like digging up old fossils?

470
00:27:08,712 --> 00:27:10,171
That's an archaeologist.

471
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:12,382
Ginger told me the whole story.

472
00:27:12,590 --> 00:27:14,092
That must be terrible, right?

473
00:27:14,301 --> 00:27:16,845
One minute you're on top of the world,
the next--

474
00:27:17,053 --> 00:27:19,306
- Guy turns out to be a crook.
- Yeah.

475
00:27:19,514 --> 00:27:21,891
Her husband, he owned racehorses.

476
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,727
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

477
00:27:23,935 --> 00:27:26,938
Oh, yes, yes, for a year or two...

478
00:27:27,147 --> 00:27:29,649
...Hal became quite obsessed
with thoroughbreds.

479
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:32,319
So, what are you gonna study
in college?

480
00:27:32,527 --> 00:27:33,570
Let me guess.

481
00:27:34,279 --> 00:27:36,072
A nurse.

482
00:27:36,531 --> 00:27:38,616
Is that how I impress you?

483
00:27:38,825 --> 00:27:41,870
- A nurse?
- You got something against nurses?

484
00:27:42,078 --> 00:27:45,415
- My sister's a nurse.
- Nurses are very hot to go to bed with.

485
00:27:45,623 --> 00:27:48,793
They have extensive knowledge
of how the human body works.

486
00:27:49,002 --> 00:27:53,089
- Careful what you accuse my sister of.
- Just saying, I know a few good nurses.

487
00:27:53,298 --> 00:27:55,342
Chili, why don't you
change the subject?

488
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:58,386
You think you're being charming,
but you're not.

489
00:27:58,595 --> 00:28:00,972
You always stare into space like that?

490
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:03,850
I had a friend who used to do that...

491
00:28:04,059 --> 00:28:07,187
...but there was something wrong
with him. He was epileptic.

492
00:28:08,271 --> 00:28:10,774
I'm not epileptic.

493
00:28:11,775 --> 00:28:14,903
If you see the waitress,
I'd like another Stoli martini.

494
00:28:15,111 --> 00:28:17,447
- What are you gonna study?
- Leave her alone.

495
00:28:17,655 --> 00:28:20,909
- It's like the third time you asked.
- So? She hasn't answered.

496
00:28:21,117 --> 00:28:24,245
I don't know, but I'll be sure
to keep you informed.

497
00:28:24,454 --> 00:28:28,833
- Oh, okay, sorry. I'll back off.
- I'm sorry, I don't mean to be curt.

498
00:28:29,042 --> 00:28:32,295
I just don't know what I'm gonna do
with the rest of my life.

499
00:28:32,504 --> 00:28:35,840
- What do you wanna do?
- Why don't we take her to see the sights?

500
00:28:36,049 --> 00:28:39,886
Then back to my place. She likes vodka.
My buddy's just back from Russia.

501
00:28:40,095 --> 00:28:42,555
- Brought me this incredible vodka.
- Great idea.

502
00:28:42,764 --> 00:28:46,142
- You're gonna love my place.
- Yeah, let's go.

503
00:29:15,547 --> 00:29:18,758
- Wait till you try this vodka.
- All right, man.

504
00:29:18,967 --> 00:29:20,718
I wish my apartment had a garden.

505
00:29:20,927 --> 00:29:23,555
- We didn't take her inside Alcatraz.
- Thank you.

506
00:29:23,763 --> 00:29:27,767
- They got tours in there, Jasmine.
- Ginger said your ex-husband did time?

507
00:29:27,976 --> 00:29:31,396
He'd still be doing time
if he didn't hang himself in his cell.

508
00:29:31,604 --> 00:29:35,316
- Really? Like with a belt?
- Well, it had to be a belt. Or a bedsheet.

509
00:29:35,525 --> 00:29:36,985
- Could be a bedsheet.
- No.

510
00:29:37,193 --> 00:29:41,531
He managed to get a piece of rope.

511
00:29:42,532 --> 00:29:43,908
Plain rope.

512
00:29:44,117 --> 00:29:46,119
You can get anything if you gotjuice.

513
00:29:46,327 --> 00:29:48,913
That's some way to go.
Strangle yourself to death?

514
00:29:49,122 --> 00:29:51,583
No, it wasn't strangulation.

515
00:29:51,791 --> 00:29:54,461
When you hang yourself,
your neck breaks.

516
00:29:54,669 --> 00:29:57,547
I wouldn't feel sorry for him.
He hurt a lot of people.

517
00:29:57,755 --> 00:30:00,800
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah, including me and Augie and her.

518
00:30:01,009 --> 00:30:04,179
A lot of people are under
the misapprehension you strangle...

519
00:30:04,387 --> 00:30:07,223
...but your neck snaps.
- Okay, we got it.

520
00:30:07,765 --> 00:30:09,726
He was a bad guy, you know?

521
00:30:09,934 --> 00:30:12,479
He lived like a big shot
on other people's money.

522
00:30:12,687 --> 00:30:16,107
- And he played around behind her back.
- No.

523
00:30:16,316 --> 00:30:19,486
- Jasmine, go and start your cooldown.
- Oh, good.

524
00:30:22,489 --> 00:30:23,907
- Hey, Jas.
- Yeah?

525
00:30:24,115 --> 00:30:27,035
I know you don't wanna go
to the Yankee game tonight.

526
00:30:27,243 --> 00:30:31,706
I'd go to any sporting event with you,
you know, but I just never got baseball.

527
00:30:31,915 --> 00:30:36,169
- I thought I'd ask Melanie. She's a fan.
- Oh, sure. God, she'll be thrilled.

528
00:30:36,377 --> 00:30:37,629
- Hey, Mel?
- Yeah?

529
00:30:37,837 --> 00:30:40,465
- You like baseball, right?
- I love baseball. Why?

530
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:45,094
I got two season tickets
behind the Yankee dugout for tonight.

531
00:30:45,303 --> 00:30:48,139
I don't have anybody else to go with me.
Are you free?

532
00:30:48,348 --> 00:30:50,975
Absolutely, if you're sure
there's nobody else.

533
00:30:51,184 --> 00:30:52,352
No.

534
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:55,688
- No, no, you'll do just fine.
- All right, thanks.

535
00:30:58,149 --> 00:31:00,068
- This is where you live? Nice.
- Yeah.

536
00:31:00,276 --> 00:31:03,488
- Hey, can you grab the groceries for me?
- Yeah.

537
00:31:09,786 --> 00:31:11,746
- I can get this one.
- Get them.

538
00:31:11,955 --> 00:31:14,249
- You got it? All right.
- I got it.

539
00:31:16,251 --> 00:31:18,336
- Oh, no.
- That's okay, don't worry.

540
00:31:18,545 --> 00:31:21,089
- No more vodka for you.
- I didn't have any vodka.

541
00:31:21,297 --> 00:31:23,550
- I didn't have no vodka.
- I know about you.

542
00:31:23,758 --> 00:31:26,094
Hey, hey, come here,
come here, come here.

543
00:31:26,302 --> 00:31:27,554
- Take it upstairs?
- Yes?

544
00:31:27,762 --> 00:31:28,888
- Yeah.
- All right.

545
00:31:29,389 --> 00:31:31,474
Eddie wants your phone number.

546
00:31:32,725 --> 00:31:34,686
- Why?
- I think he wants to call you.

547
00:31:34,894 --> 00:31:37,730
I think he wants to ask you out,
you know, for dinner.

548
00:31:37,939 --> 00:31:41,526
- Look, I'm busy at the moment.
- He's a terrific guy. Look at him.

549
00:31:41,734 --> 00:31:43,945
Well, why doesn't he ask me himself?

550
00:31:44,153 --> 00:31:47,073
Because he's shy, you know?
He thinks he's short.

551
00:31:49,158 --> 00:31:52,078
Look, I'm concentrating
on school, okay?

552
00:31:52,287 --> 00:31:54,122
- And getting a job.
- That's perfect.

553
00:31:54,330 --> 00:31:56,291
Right, he knows this dentist.

554
00:31:56,499 --> 00:31:59,377
No, I have no interest
in being a receptionist.

555
00:31:59,586 --> 00:32:01,921
What did you have in mind,
running a bank?

556
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:05,883
- Is this what you wanted to talk about?
- And how long you're planning...

557
00:32:06,092 --> 00:32:09,762
...on staying with Ginger.
- Oh, right. It's just till I find my feet

558
00:32:09,971 --> 00:32:11,389
We have a lot of big plans.

559
00:32:11,598 --> 00:32:14,434
Don't worry, I'm not gonna ruin
any of your big plans.

560
00:32:14,642 --> 00:32:17,395
No one wants to get out of here
as fast as I do.

561
00:32:17,604 --> 00:32:20,815
I'm sure this is a big comedown
from what you're used to.

562
00:32:21,024 --> 00:32:24,569
It's fine. it's-- I'm grateful for her help.

563
00:32:24,777 --> 00:32:26,696
So you don't want Eddie to call you?

564
00:32:26,904 --> 00:32:30,366
No, I'm not ready to go out
at the moment.

565
00:32:31,576 --> 00:32:34,329
Ginger said
you had a nervous breakdown.

566
00:32:37,457 --> 00:32:39,125
She tends to be quite dramatic.

567
00:32:39,334 --> 00:32:41,961
Said you were in the street,
talking to yourself.

568
00:32:44,881 --> 00:32:48,676
You know, I don't think
that this is any of your business.

569
00:32:48,885 --> 00:32:53,056
No, but since I'm marrying her,
we don't have any secrets between us.

570
00:32:58,978 --> 00:33:01,064
- What did Chili want?
- Oh, nothing.

571
00:33:01,272 --> 00:33:05,360
His retarded boyfriend wanted a date,
but he was too shy to ask.

572
00:33:05,568 --> 00:33:09,280
- What do you think of Chili?
- He's very anxious to move in with you.

573
00:33:09,489 --> 00:33:11,699
Yeah, I know. He's got the hots for me.

574
00:33:11,908 --> 00:33:13,409
Can I speak frankly?

575
00:33:13,618 --> 00:33:15,370
- You hate him?
- Yeah.

576
00:33:15,578 --> 00:33:18,081
I could tell you two didn't hit it off.

577
00:33:18,289 --> 00:33:21,709
He's another version of Augie.
He's a loser.

578
00:33:21,918 --> 00:33:25,296
Hey, didn't I hear Eddie say
he knows a dentist looking for help?

579
00:33:25,505 --> 00:33:29,133
Oh, forget it! Jesus, it's too menial!

580
00:33:29,342 --> 00:33:31,344
I'd go nuts.

581
00:33:32,428 --> 00:33:34,847
I wanna go back to school.

582
00:33:35,056 --> 00:33:40,937
I wanna get my degree and become,
you know, something substantial.

583
00:33:41,187 --> 00:33:44,065
I can't just do some mindless job.

584
00:33:44,273 --> 00:33:47,443
I was forced to take a job selling shoes
on Madison Avenue.

585
00:33:47,652 --> 00:33:50,488
Oh, so humiliating.

586
00:33:50,697 --> 00:33:54,409
Friends I'd had at dinner parties
at our apartment came in...

587
00:33:54,617 --> 00:33:58,579
...and I waited on them. I mean,
do you have any idea what that's like?

588
00:33:58,788 --> 00:34:02,458
You know, one minute,
you're hosting women...

589
00:34:02,667 --> 00:34:06,713
...and the next, you're measuring
their shoe size and fitting them.

590
00:34:07,255 --> 00:34:09,424
Erica Bishop came into the store.

591
00:34:09,632 --> 00:34:13,594
She saw me
and was so embarrassed for me...

592
00:34:13,803 --> 00:34:17,014
...she slipped out
thinking I didn't see her.

593
00:34:17,348 --> 00:34:20,309
I saw you, Erica!

594
00:34:22,311 --> 00:34:24,272
Are you okay?

595
00:34:25,356 --> 00:34:27,942
Hey, you got great taste.

596
00:34:28,151 --> 00:34:32,697
Maybe you could do something
in fashion.

597
00:34:32,905 --> 00:34:34,323
Or designing. Yeah?

598
00:34:35,533 --> 00:34:37,785
- Yeah, that's true.
- Yeah.

599
00:34:37,994 --> 00:34:41,080
Everyone used to say
I'd make a good interior decorator.

600
00:34:42,540 --> 00:34:45,084
There's courses,
but, you know, they cost money.

601
00:34:45,293 --> 00:34:49,297
No, Eve Logan
got her decorator's license online.

602
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:51,507
On a computer?

603
00:34:51,716 --> 00:34:53,092
I guess you could, but--

604
00:34:53,301 --> 00:34:56,679
Yeah, I'm so computer illiterate.

605
00:34:57,555 --> 00:34:59,766
But I could take a class in computers.

606
00:34:59,974 --> 00:35:04,687
And then when I can handle a computer,
then I can study decorating online.

607
00:35:04,896 --> 00:35:09,233
- That sounds too complicated.
- Why is your reaction always negative?

608
00:35:09,442 --> 00:35:11,068
I'm just saying.

609
00:35:11,277 --> 00:35:13,654
You know, first you gotta
learn computers...

610
00:35:13,863 --> 00:35:16,491
...and then go for a decorator's
license online.

611
00:35:16,699 --> 00:35:19,869
You're afraid I'll stay here too long.

612
00:35:20,077 --> 00:35:21,829
No, you know--

613
00:35:22,038 --> 00:35:25,333
Just all those courses,
they cost money.

614
00:35:26,375 --> 00:35:30,922
You'll work out here. It's mostly phones
and keeping my appointments straight.

615
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:34,217
There's the follow-up cards,
which I explained...

616
00:35:34,425 --> 00:35:37,136
...and the notices for cleanings.

617
00:35:37,637 --> 00:35:39,472
Any questions?

618
00:35:40,515 --> 00:35:43,184
Tell Dr. Flicker it's an emergency.

619
00:35:43,392 --> 00:35:46,729
- Come on, come on.
- Yes?

620
00:35:47,814 --> 00:35:48,856
What?

621
00:35:49,065 --> 00:35:51,025
Yes, a cancellation.

622
00:35:51,234 --> 00:35:53,861
Oh, you want to cancel.

623
00:35:54,070 --> 00:35:55,530
- When?
- Please.

624
00:35:55,738 --> 00:35:59,450
Wait, wait, wait. You said the 24th.

625
00:35:59,659 --> 00:36:01,494
My husband has an abscess.

626
00:36:01,911 --> 00:36:05,206
Can you just put someone on
who speaks better English?

627
00:36:05,414 --> 00:36:10,002
The software interface
is what provides you, the user...

628
00:36:10,211 --> 00:36:13,673
...the ability to control the hardware,
the computer.

629
00:36:13,881 --> 00:36:15,550
Okay, that's the operating.

630
00:36:15,758 --> 00:36:19,679
The operating system
gives you that ability.

631
00:36:19,887 --> 00:36:21,848
I need an appointment in two weeks.

632
00:36:27,770 --> 00:36:30,398
Is the 10th good for you?

633
00:36:30,606 --> 00:36:33,568
The 10th. Yes, fine.

634
00:36:33,776 --> 00:36:36,028
Oh, better make it the 12th.

635
00:36:36,237 --> 00:36:39,407
- Oh, we're all booked on the 12th.
- Okay.

636
00:36:39,615 --> 00:36:40,908
Make it the 14th.

637
00:36:41,617 --> 00:36:43,411
- The 14th?
- Oh, no.

638
00:36:43,619 --> 00:36:45,705
Is 3 good on the 9th?

639
00:36:45,913 --> 00:36:47,874
Or noon on the 11th?

640
00:36:48,082 --> 00:36:52,128
Can you just settle on a time, please?
Just pick a time.

641
00:36:52,962 --> 00:36:55,631
Remember the yoga class.

642
00:36:57,800 --> 00:36:59,844
Deep breath.

643
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:02,805
Breathe deeply.

644
00:37:03,806 --> 00:37:07,768
All right, deep breath.

645
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:13,900
If you take a deep breath,
you can smell the honeysuckle.

646
00:37:14,108 --> 00:37:17,028
- Beautiful. Make a great perfume.
- It would.

647
00:37:17,236 --> 00:37:19,780
- Your polo pony's in great shape.
- Thank you.

648
00:37:19,989 --> 00:37:22,325
- No, I have never seen a polo match.
- Really?

649
00:37:22,533 --> 00:37:26,913
My husband's a fanatic. Not to say
he's good at it, but it keeps him busy.

650
00:37:27,121 --> 00:37:28,664
We got a flight to catch.

651
00:37:28,873 --> 00:37:31,417
Hal's taking Danny to Augusta
for the Masters.

652
00:37:31,626 --> 00:37:34,170
They're golf degenerates.
I'll be home alone.

653
00:37:34,378 --> 00:37:37,048
- We'll be back in three days.
- Did we tell you?

654
00:37:37,256 --> 00:37:39,634
- Danny was first in his class at Harvard.
- No.

655
00:37:39,842 --> 00:37:41,010
- Yes.
- Congratulations.

656
00:37:41,218 --> 00:37:42,720
- Thanks.
- He's a math genius.

657
00:37:42,929 --> 00:37:46,390
He's the genius. Dad did a guest lecture
at the business school...

658
00:37:46,599 --> 00:37:48,976
...and everyone said
it was the best lecture.

659
00:37:49,185 --> 00:37:52,104
Naturally I became an instant
celebrity on campus.

660
00:37:52,313 --> 00:37:55,107
Hey, I need your signature
onthese,baby.

661
00:37:56,859 --> 00:38:01,489
Be careful. Don't get hit by a golf ball.
That's how Ray Becker died.

662
00:38:01,697 --> 00:38:04,992
You know, a little blue bruise
on his temple.

663
00:38:14,710 --> 00:38:18,506
What are you always studying
in your spare time?

664
00:38:18,714 --> 00:38:21,300
Well, I'm trying to learn
to use a computer.

665
00:38:21,509 --> 00:38:24,804
I wanna study interior design online.

666
00:38:25,012 --> 00:38:27,139
Oh, you wanna be a decorator?

667
00:38:27,348 --> 00:38:29,475
Yeah, it's where my strongest gifts are.

668
00:38:29,684 --> 00:38:32,520
You know, I have a natural flair
for space and color...

669
00:38:32,728 --> 00:38:35,523
...and an eye for choosing
soft furnishings.

670
00:38:35,731 --> 00:38:39,944
It's very commendable, but I can't really
have you studying on work time...

671
00:38:40,152 --> 00:38:42,530
...if it interferes
with the business at hand.

672
00:38:42,738 --> 00:38:45,324
Yes. I'm sorry. It won't happen again.

673
00:38:45,533 --> 00:38:47,576
Please, see that it doesn't.

674
00:38:49,745 --> 00:38:55,543
- I was gonna ask you a question.
- Yes?

675
00:38:57,169 --> 00:39:00,256
Would you have a drink with me?

676
00:39:00,798 --> 00:39:02,550
A drink?

677
00:39:04,093 --> 00:39:05,970
I'd love it if you could.

678
00:39:06,512 --> 00:39:09,265
Well, it would have to be a quick one...

679
00:39:09,473 --> 00:39:13,227
...because, you know,
I'm meeting my boyfriend for dinner.

680
00:39:17,023 --> 00:39:18,190
I was just saying...

681
00:39:18,399 --> 00:39:22,028
...you can tell awful lot about people
when you look in their mouths.

682
00:39:22,236 --> 00:39:26,407
Are they conscientious?
Are they disciplined? Are they vain?

683
00:39:26,615 --> 00:39:29,410
Or careless?
You have to know what to look for.

684
00:39:29,618 --> 00:39:32,413
Do you have the time?
I have to keep an eye on it.

685
00:39:32,621 --> 00:39:33,664
I've got homework.

686
00:39:33,873 --> 00:39:38,878
This computer thing is proving
a little more difficult than I imagined.

687
00:39:39,086 --> 00:39:43,674
It's funny, really, because I used to be
a straight-A student in college.

688
00:39:43,883 --> 00:39:47,887
You know, but they say every year,
millions of brain cells just die off.

689
00:39:48,095 --> 00:39:50,139
You have good teeth.

690
00:39:51,974 --> 00:39:54,143
I'm sure you get
many compliments on them.

691
00:39:54,351 --> 00:39:57,021
- Well, thank you.
- Yeah.

692
00:39:57,313 --> 00:40:00,524
You know,
you're a very beautiful woman.

693
00:40:01,233 --> 00:40:03,444
Are you serious with your boyfriend?

694
00:40:04,945 --> 00:40:06,947
I don't mean to pry.

695
00:40:09,492 --> 00:40:13,120
God, life is complicated.

696
00:40:13,454 --> 00:40:15,623
Have you ever had any children?

697
00:40:15,831 --> 00:40:18,918
How do you expect me to react
when my father is unmasked...

698
00:40:19,126 --> 00:40:22,213
...as a common thief?
