01:18:59,152 --> 01:19:00,946
Who's Ellen?

1375
01:19:10,038 --> 01:19:11,456
Yeah, I--

1376
01:19:11,665 --> 01:19:14,251
I didn't understand you had a wife.

1377
01:19:16,670 --> 01:19:18,130
No.

1378
01:19:18,839 --> 01:19:20,966
No, you never said.

1379
01:19:36,356 --> 01:19:38,358
My mother was very impressed
with you.

1380
01:19:38,567 --> 01:19:40,777
- Really?
- Yeah. You two had a discussion...

1381
01:19:40,986 --> 01:19:43,905
...about her collection of pewter.
- Yes. I love pewter.

1382
01:19:44,114 --> 01:19:47,075
Hal used to have his beer
out of a pewter mug.

1383
01:19:47,534 --> 01:19:48,660
And your dad?

1384
01:19:48,869 --> 01:19:52,873
My dad can be very critical sometimes,
but he was very taken with you.

1385
01:19:53,582 --> 01:19:56,626
Well, don't worry,
I won't pick out too big a stone.

1386
01:19:56,835 --> 01:19:59,254
Yeah, nothing larger
than the Hope diamond.

1387
01:19:59,463 --> 01:20:01,715
Hey, Jasmine.

1388
01:20:03,008 --> 01:20:05,886
What? You don't remember me?

1389
01:20:06,678 --> 01:20:09,639
Of course I remember you.
What a surprise.

1390
01:20:10,557 --> 01:20:12,809
Yeah, surprise, surprise, huh?

1391
01:20:13,560 --> 01:20:15,770
This is Augie. Dwight.

1392
01:20:15,979 --> 01:20:17,814
- Dwight, hi.
- How you doing?

1393
01:20:18,023 --> 01:20:19,691
I was married to her sister.

1394
01:20:20,317 --> 01:20:22,110
- Okay.
- Years ago. Years.

1395
01:20:22,319 --> 01:20:25,363
Wasn't that many years.
She makes it sound ancient.

1396
01:20:25,572 --> 01:20:29,201
Congratulations. Ginger said
you got a new job up in Alaska.

1397
01:20:30,702 --> 01:20:33,538
I could've had my own company
if it wasn't for you...

1398
01:20:33,747 --> 01:20:37,792
...and that crook you married.
- I don't think it's the time and place.

1399
01:20:38,001 --> 01:20:42,714
Oh, really? You think I wanna lay oil pipe
way the hell up there in Alaska?

1400
01:20:42,923 --> 01:20:44,299
I got no money.

1401
01:20:44,508 --> 01:20:47,886
Christ, can't you put this behind you
and move on? I've moved on.

1402
01:20:48,094 --> 01:20:52,265
- Take it easy. I don't know who you are--
- Right, you don't, so stay out of it.

1403
01:20:52,849 --> 01:20:54,100
I saw your son.

1404
01:20:55,268 --> 01:20:57,687
Yeah, that's right, Danny.
Remember him?

1405
01:20:58,230 --> 01:21:02,567
Lives across the bridge in Oakland,
works at a music store. Antonio's.

1406
01:21:03,109 --> 01:21:06,112
He's doing pretty good. He's married.

1407
01:21:06,655 --> 01:21:09,199
I think he's finally over Hal's suicide.

1408
01:21:09,783 --> 01:21:12,077
Danny's in Oakland?

1409
01:21:12,285 --> 01:21:16,081
Let me tell you something,
Jeanette, Jasmine...

1410
01:21:16,289 --> 01:21:19,251
...whatever it is
you call yourself these days.

1411
01:21:19,459 --> 01:21:21,419
Some people...

1412
01:21:21,628 --> 01:21:25,131
...they don't put things behind
so easily.

1413
01:21:33,139 --> 01:21:34,891
You have a son?

1414
01:21:35,809 --> 01:21:40,146
Yes, I have a son. He's not-- Biologically
he's not my son. He's my step--

1415
01:21:40,355 --> 01:21:42,649
- Hal's suicide?
- I can explain it all later.

1416
01:21:42,857 --> 01:21:45,694
- Can we just--?
- Not until you tell me what's going on.

1417
01:21:45,902 --> 01:21:47,737
- Not in the street.
- I want to know.

1418
01:21:47,946 --> 01:21:50,615
- I know. We'll go somewhere quiet.
- Get in the car.

1419
01:21:50,824 --> 01:21:53,785
- Don't talk to me in that tone of voice.
- Okay.

1420
01:21:58,832 --> 01:22:02,377
Of course we can't get married!
You lied to me up and down the line!

1421
01:22:02,586 --> 01:22:05,213
- No, I wanted to tell you.
- Are you delusional?

1422
01:22:05,422 --> 01:22:07,340
Didn't you think I'd find out?

1423
01:22:07,549 --> 01:22:10,635
- What were you thinking?
- I don't know what I was thinking.

1424
01:22:10,844 --> 01:22:13,972
Everything happened in the past.
You and I loved each other.

1425
01:22:14,180 --> 01:22:15,849
What? That it would just vanish?

1426
01:22:16,057 --> 01:22:19,811
Didn't you think I would find out,
if not today, eventually?

1427
01:22:20,020 --> 01:22:24,566
Like after we were married? Is that what
you wanted, to wait until it was too late?

1428
01:22:24,774 --> 01:22:27,902
For your future plans
where you needed the appropriate wife?

1429
01:22:28,111 --> 01:22:31,615
I won't say it wouldn't be an issue,
but that you could stand by...

1430
01:22:31,823 --> 01:22:35,368
...deceive me until I married you--
- No, you mean till I trapped you.

1431
01:22:35,577 --> 01:22:39,831
- Your ethical behavior is equal to your ex.
- I wasn't deceiving you. I loved you.

1432
01:22:40,040 --> 01:22:43,793
- I found out by chance, by sheer chance.
- Okay, if it's over, it's over.

1433
01:22:44,002 --> 01:22:47,422
I get it. You're not marrying me.
I brought everything on myself.

1434
01:22:47,631 --> 01:22:51,843
I've only got myself to blame.
I did it to myself again, as usual.

1435
01:22:52,052 --> 01:22:54,679
You and your stupid
little French whore.

1436
01:22:54,888 --> 01:22:58,683
- I have no idea what you're talking about.
- Let me out of the car.

1437
01:22:58,892 --> 01:23:01,603
- Let me out of the car.
- How are you gonna get home?

1438
01:23:01,811 --> 01:23:04,731
I'm not going home. Let me out.
Let me out of the car!

1439
01:23:26,503 --> 01:23:29,881
Hey, remember to tell her
when she gets here, okay?

1440
01:23:30,090 --> 01:23:31,925
Believe me, she won't care.

1441
01:23:32,133 --> 01:23:34,886
- She is half out the door.
- Yeah, well...

1442
01:23:35,095 --> 01:23:37,055
I didn't start out not liking her.

1443
01:23:37,263 --> 01:23:40,266
I think she had it in for me
from the moment she met me.

1444
01:23:41,101 --> 01:23:42,310
Well, I like you.

1445
01:23:42,519 --> 01:23:45,438
Now, that's what counts,
not how she feels about you.

1446
01:23:45,647 --> 01:23:48,316
You know, I'm sick of her
calling you a loser...

1447
01:23:48,525 --> 01:23:51,861
...or always pushing me
to find a better man.

1448
01:23:52,070 --> 01:23:55,198
You know, in my book, you're no loser.

1449
01:23:55,407 --> 01:23:58,410
You're twice the guy I met at the party
she dragged me to.

1450
01:23:58,618 --> 01:24:00,412
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1451
01:24:00,620 --> 01:24:02,163
- Well, I love you.
- I know.

1452
01:24:02,372 --> 01:24:05,917
- I love the boys. I think they love me too.
- They do.

1453
01:24:06,126 --> 01:24:10,505
- When I thought I lost you--
- You didn't lose me, baby.

1454
01:24:10,714 --> 01:24:12,924
I almost lost you.

1455
01:24:40,326 --> 01:24:43,371
Is this what you gave up
everything for?

1456
01:24:43,580 --> 01:24:47,292
To sell secondhand
musical instruments?

1457
01:24:48,710 --> 01:24:52,172
I asked Augie not to tell you
where I was.

1458
01:24:54,132 --> 01:24:55,842
Why?

1459
01:24:57,343 --> 01:24:59,345
What happened?

1460
01:25:00,054 --> 01:25:02,807
Why did you disappear like that
and never contact me?

1461
01:25:03,016 --> 01:25:06,519
I couldn't find you when I needed you.

1462
01:25:07,103 --> 01:25:11,983
I know the whole story, I found it out,
so don't act so surprised.

1463
01:25:19,824 --> 01:25:22,869
Are you having an affair
with Lisette Boudreau?

1464
01:25:23,369 --> 01:25:25,705
Oh, Jasmine,
I can't do this without a drink.

1465
01:25:25,914 --> 01:25:28,833
No, don't tap dance.
You never went to Chicago.

1466
01:25:29,042 --> 01:25:31,377
You took the Jordans' au pair
to Paris.

1467
01:25:31,586 --> 01:25:33,838
I know what's been going on.

1468
01:25:34,214 --> 01:25:37,801
- Can we talk about this, please?
- You bet we can talk about it.

1469
01:25:38,009 --> 01:25:39,511
Can you do it calmly?

1470
01:25:39,719 --> 01:25:43,348
I wanna talk to you about
what's going on, but you're always so--

1471
01:25:43,556 --> 01:25:45,141
How do you expect me to react?

1472
01:25:45,350 --> 01:25:47,852
You've been sleeping
with other women for years.

1473
01:25:48,061 --> 01:25:52,106
I mean, Raylene,
your secretary, our trainer.

1474
01:25:52,315 --> 01:25:54,859
- Amy.
- This is different.

1475
01:25:55,068 --> 01:25:56,945
This is serious.

1476
01:25:57,195 --> 01:25:59,322
Lisette and I are in love.

1477
01:26:00,198 --> 01:26:02,158
Wha--? What?

1478
01:26:02,450 --> 01:26:03,785
Are you crazy?

1479
01:26:03,993 --> 01:26:08,081
I'm sorry, but I need you to hear
what I'm saying. Lisette and I are in love.

1480
01:26:08,748 --> 01:26:11,835
What does that mean?
What does that stupidity even mean?

1481
01:26:12,043 --> 01:26:15,964
It means that we are making plans
for the future together.

1482
01:26:16,172 --> 01:26:18,466
I'm sorry.
I'm having trouble understanding.

1483
01:26:18,675 --> 01:26:22,053
I know this comes as a shock,
but I have to be honest with you.

1484
01:26:22,262 --> 01:26:25,640
You wanna be honest.
That's the biggest joke of all.

1485
01:26:25,849 --> 01:26:27,976
I've had casual flirtations in the past.

1486
01:26:28,184 --> 01:26:31,020
They didn't mean anything until now.
This is different.

1487
01:26:31,229 --> 01:26:35,525
Are you out of your mind?
She is a teenager, for chrissake.

1488
01:26:35,733 --> 01:26:38,403
She's an au pair.
I mean, are you crazy?

1489
01:26:38,611 --> 01:26:43,074
- Christ, this is hard for me to tell you!
- It's hard for you? What about me?

1490
01:26:43,283 --> 01:26:45,159
This is so humiliating for me.

1491
01:26:45,368 --> 01:26:48,913
I mean, it is bad enough that
everyone knows you've been unfaithful.

1492
01:26:49,122 --> 01:26:52,500
But to throw me away for this
stupid-looking little French--

1493
01:26:52,709 --> 01:26:55,545
- I will take very good care of you.
- I'm sorry.

1494
01:26:55,753 --> 01:26:59,173
I can't breathe. I can't breathe.

1495
01:26:59,382 --> 01:27:02,093
I don't know what I'm--
What am I doing here?

1496
01:27:02,302 --> 01:27:06,306
Oh, God, this is unacceptable.
This is not gonna happen.

1497
01:27:06,514 --> 01:27:09,017
You're not going anywhere.
This is unacceptable.

1498
01:27:09,225 --> 01:27:12,979
- Jasmine, you're having a tantrum.
- Don't you touch me!

1499
01:27:13,187 --> 01:27:16,107
- Don't you touch me!
- You are having a tantrum.

1500
01:27:16,316 --> 01:27:18,818
Stop, S'loP-

1501
01:27:19,027 --> 01:27:21,738
- What am I doing here?
- Pull yourself together.

1502
01:27:22,322 --> 01:27:24,282
- I can't--
- Jasmine.

1503
01:27:27,493 --> 01:27:31,122
When you calm down, we can talk
like two civilized adults...

1504
01:27:31,331 --> 01:27:33,917
...about the arrangements
we have to make.

1505
01:27:46,888 --> 01:27:49,557
Until then I'm gonna check into a hotel.

1506
01:27:56,981 --> 01:28:01,861
What am I doing here?
What am I doing here?

1507
01:28:13,790 --> 01:28:18,169
Hello.
Yes, I want the number of the FBI.

1508
01:28:18,920 --> 01:28:20,797
Can you connect me?

1509
01:28:22,382 --> 01:28:24,384
The FBI.

1510
01:28:24,842 --> 01:28:27,011
- Mr. Francis?
- Yes?

1511
01:28:27,220 --> 01:28:28,846
- Hal Francis?
- Yes.

1512
01:28:29,055 --> 01:28:32,141
I'm sorry, sir,
we have a warrant for your arrest.

1513
01:28:32,475 --> 01:28:34,811
- What?
- We have a warrant for your arrest.

1514
01:28:35,019 --> 01:28:37,480
- Is this some kind of a joke?
- No, sir.

1515
01:28:37,689 --> 01:28:40,858
- It's best if you come with us now.
- Under arrest for what?

1516
01:28:41,067 --> 01:28:43,653
Sir, come with us now.
We'll settle this downtown.

1517
01:28:43,861 --> 01:28:46,072
- Do you have a warrant?
- I do.

1518
01:28:47,198 --> 01:28:48,616
- Gonna handcuff me?
- We are.

1519
01:28:48,825 --> 01:28:52,161
- I wanna talk to my lawyer.
- You'll be able to call your lawyer.

1520
01:28:52,370 --> 01:28:55,289
But we'll warn you,
you have the right to remain silent.

1521
01:28:55,498 --> 01:28:58,292
Anything you say can be held
against you in court.

1522
01:28:58,501 --> 01:29:00,378
- Okay, okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

1523
01:29:00,586 --> 01:29:04,132
Jesus Christ Almighty.

1524
01:29:04,799 --> 01:29:09,679
- What am I being arrested for?
- We can discuss this downtown, sir.

1525
01:29:12,390 --> 01:29:17,061
As disillusioned as I was with him,
I hated you more.

1526
01:29:20,106 --> 01:29:23,735
The moment I did what I did,
I regretted it.

1527
01:29:24,444 --> 01:29:27,572
I don't wanna discuss it.
It's past. It's over.

1528
01:29:27,780 --> 01:29:30,366
You can't take back that phone call.

1529
01:29:32,201 --> 01:29:34,454
I need you, Danny.

1530
01:29:35,705 --> 01:29:39,584
I don't wanna see you, Jasmine.
I want the past past.

1531
01:29:39,792 --> 01:29:43,755
I've become a different person,
thanks to my wife. I'm off drugs.

1532
01:29:43,963 --> 01:29:47,633
Just, please, don't spoil everything.

1533
01:29:47,842 --> 01:29:50,678
Just get out of my life
so I can move on.

1534
01:29:52,930 --> 01:29:54,640
Definitely.

1535
01:29:56,684 --> 01:29:57,769
_H6Y-
_H6Y-

1536
01:29:57,977 --> 01:30:00,980
Hey, have some champagne.

1537
01:30:01,647 --> 01:30:04,442
Chili brought some over to celebrate.

1538
01:30:04,650 --> 01:30:06,694
We're back together.

1539
01:30:08,029 --> 01:30:10,948
I'm sorry,
I'm not in a celebratory mood.

1540
01:30:11,157 --> 01:30:14,368
I don't think I'd find that news
anything to celebrate about.

1541
01:30:14,577 --> 01:30:17,580
Hey, come on, Jasmine,
let's not dig at each other, okay?

1542
01:30:17,789 --> 01:30:20,666
I'm moving in, and she tells me
you found a rich husband.

1543
01:30:20,875 --> 01:30:23,377
- Gonna be a big shot in Washington.
- We made up.

1544
01:30:23,586 --> 01:30:27,799
- Yeah, she begged for my forgiveness.
- And he cried like a baby and apologized.

1545
01:30:28,007 --> 01:30:32,929
- I didn't cry.
- Bullshit. You cry all the time.

1546
01:30:33,137 --> 01:30:35,306
But we're moving in.

1547
01:30:35,515 --> 01:30:39,393
It's something we planned for a long time
and maybe if we'd just done it--

1548
01:30:39,602 --> 01:30:42,105
Oh, for chrissake.

1549
01:30:42,313 --> 01:30:44,774
What's wrong with your self-esteem?

1550
01:30:44,982 --> 01:30:48,986
There's men who'd never think
about ripping the phone out of the wall.

1551
01:30:49,195 --> 01:30:52,740
Hey, leave him alone.
You're always picking on him.

1552
01:30:52,949 --> 01:30:54,867
No, you choose losers, okay?

1553
01:30:55,076 --> 01:30:57,370
Because that's what you think
you deserve.

1554
01:30:57,578 --> 01:31:01,958
That's why you're living like this and
that's why you'll never have a better life.

1555
01:31:02,458 --> 01:31:04,377
I'm-- I'm living--

1556
01:31:04,585 --> 01:31:10,341
I'm living like this because
you married the biggest loser of all...

1557
01:31:10,550 --> 01:31:12,844
...and went your own sweet way...

1558
01:31:13,052 --> 01:31:18,599
...while he pissed away my
one big chance to make a better life.

1559
01:31:18,808 --> 01:31:21,310
Come on, let's not ruin
our celebration, okay?

1560
01:31:21,519 --> 01:31:25,189
Come on, she's happy, we're happy.
Let's let sleeping dogs lie.

1561
01:31:25,398 --> 01:31:28,860
He's right. I'm not gonna be drawn
into defending myself...

1562
01:31:29,068 --> 01:31:32,905
...when all I wanted to do
was bring you in on a good deal.

1563
01:31:35,074 --> 01:31:38,035
I'm moving out of this place today.

1564
01:31:38,536 --> 01:31:40,705
I just gotta get myself together.

1565
01:31:40,913 --> 01:31:45,418
Dwight asked me to move in with him,
as I expected he would.

1566
01:31:45,626 --> 01:31:47,795
He wants me to finish
decorating his home.

1567
01:31:48,004 --> 01:31:50,548
Then we'll marry
and we'll move in together.

1568
01:31:50,756 --> 01:31:53,676
He's one of these men
who's lost without a woman.

1569
01:31:53,885 --> 01:31:56,888
It has to be the right woman,
who's a plus for his career.

1570
01:31:57,096 --> 01:32:01,517
And I have the social skills required
for his future in politics.

1571
01:32:01,893 --> 01:32:05,897
For the next few years,
we'll be living in Vienna.

1572
01:32:06,355 --> 01:32:09,567
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna take a shower.

1573
01:32:09,775 --> 01:32:11,611
I'll send for my luggage.

1574
01:32:14,947 --> 01:32:19,577
I was pretty angry at some of the things
she said, but I kept it on the inside.

1575
01:32:20,703 --> 01:32:25,625
I'm tired of her knocking you.
You know?

1576
01:32:34,008 --> 01:32:36,844
Don't even think about taking
that last slice of pizza.

1577
01:32:37,053 --> 01:32:40,640
- What? Why?
- That's my slice of pizza. Don't take it.

1578
01:32:40,848 --> 01:32:43,226
- Is it really?
- Last slice belongs to the man.

1579
01:32:43,434 --> 01:32:46,729
- You're putting too much on the hips.
- Is that so?

1580
01:32:46,938 --> 01:32:49,941
- Yeah, if you wanna keep me around--
- This slice is yours?

1581
01:32:50,149 --> 01:32:55,863
- Don't touch it. Ginger, I swear to God.
- Is this yours? Is this yours?

1582
01:32:56,072 --> 01:32:58,324
That slice of pizza is mine.

1583
01:32:59,533 --> 01:33:01,244
- That's mine.
- Yeah.

1584
01:33:01,452 --> 01:33:03,579
That's mine. That's mine.

1585
01:33:03,788 --> 01:33:06,582
Oh, that's mine.
Those are definitely mine.

1586
01:33:06,791 --> 01:33:10,378
Is that yours? Yeah?

1587
01:33:11,963 --> 01:33:14,507
Yeah, that's yours, okay.

1588
01:33:33,025 --> 01:33:35,695
It's fraught with peril.

1589
01:33:36,445 --> 01:33:39,573
They gossip, you know, they talk.

1590
01:33:41,575 --> 01:33:43,536
I saw Danny.

1591
01:33:43,869 --> 01:33:46,122
Yes, did I tell you?

1592
01:33:47,373 --> 01:33:49,583
He's getting married.

1593
01:33:51,669 --> 01:33:55,172
A weekend in Palm Beach
means I can wear...

1594
01:33:55,381 --> 01:34:00,344
What could I wear? I can wear
the Dior dress I bought in Paris.

1595
01:34:01,387 --> 01:34:04,390
Yes, my black dress.

1596
01:34:04,598 --> 01:34:07,727
Well, Hal always used to surprise me
